<br>
1. Draughts can easily be made into this spell line. Change them so all three gain 30 damage per level caping out at lvl 60 they would do 913 damage.  <br>
<br>
At 51 that’s 643 damage for 215 mana at 3.00 damage/mana with 117 damage/sec. <br>
At 55 that’s 763 damage for 215 mana at 3.50 damage/mana with 138 damage/sec. <br>
At 60 that’s 913 damage for 215 mana at 4.25 damage/mana with 166 damage/sec.<br>
<br>
2. Move sunstrike (SS) to lvl 55 with 500 manacost.  Create a new lvl 60 spell Voltaic Flare (VF) with 2032 damage for 507 mana. Change casting times on IC, SS, and VF to 4 sec. Make IC, SS, VF channelable through a grouped tank so the next successful hit the tank (warrior, paly, sk) does will proc the damage and only the tank agros, these spells can no longer just be cast straight on the mob. <br>
<br>
At 51 we’d have 1120 damage for 400 mana at 2.80 damage/mana with 172 damage/sec. <br>
At 55 we’d have 1613 damage for 487 mana at 3.31 damage/mana with 248 damage/sec. <br>
At 60 we’d have 2032 damage for 507 mana at 4.01 damage/mana with 312 damage/sec.<br>
<br>
3. Have lure of frost, flame, and lightening all three ramp up to do 900 damage at lvl 60, uliminate Lure of Ice from the game. Change manacost for all three lure spells to 285.<br>
<br>
At 51 that’d be 640 damage for 285 mana at 2.25 damage/mana with 091 damage/sec.<br>
At 55 that’d be 755 damage for 285 mana at 2.65 damage/mana with 108 damage/sec.<br>
At 60 that’d be 900 damage for 285 mana at 3.12 damage/mana with 128 damage/sec.<br>
<br>
Any comments? Think this new layout is enough to balance wizards? Have i gone to far? Not far enough?<br>
<br>
Mysthyl Endowyn<br>
Sorcerer of Drinal<br>
<br>
P.S Change Ice Spear to 260 manacost so it still has an efficiency advantage over lvl 60 draughts.<br>
P.S.S. To calculate damage/sec I used the true casting time which is cast time + 2.5 spell refresh <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 934<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/01 3:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my solution for wizard balance</span><hr size=1> Well, those are nice steps for past level 50.  Of course there are a few problems BEFORE that point, which would have to be addressed for 'balance' to occur. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvalgavgaav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valgav Gaav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/01 3:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmmm.</span><hr size=1> Sorry, i disagree with a part of it, the other ideas arnt bad though. Guess its a good news bad news based on how people play. <br>
